<div id="content" class="content wikipage" lang="en" dir="ltr">
<p id="l1">
In video and motion picture photography, <a title="Animation" href="Animation">animation</a> technique whereby a computer is used to automatically move the camera or an animation sequence a set amount of space each second (or less). Computer control of the process allows for a greater degree of accuracy and sophistication, not to mention a substantial reduction of labor on the part of the cameraman or animator. 
</p>
